Cell["\<\
Toffoli gate was invented by Tommaso Toffoli for classical reversible \
computation.\
\>", "Notes",
 CellID->1067943069,ExpressionUUID->"7fbd1c38-26e1-4939-ab1d-40c4aadb0995"],

Cell["\<\
It is universal for classical reversible computation, but is not universal \
for quantum computation.\
\>", "Notes",
 CellID->1640755739,ExpressionUUID->"65563380-02d5-4ee2-b7ec-06318d4f9660"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The Hadamard, quadrant, CNOT, and Toffoli gates form a universal set of \
gates in the sense that an arbitrary gate on ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["n", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "1af1b567-4bd5-4791-97ca-c5946808137c"],
 " qubits can be approximated to an arbitrary accuracy using a quantum \
circuit model composed of only these gates. The set still remains universal \
if the Toffoli gate is replaced by the octant gate."
}], "Notes",
 CellID->325543624,ExpressionUUID->"fef0933a-b306-4450-8715-01bb326f6c88"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In fact, the Toffoli and Hadamard gates form a smaller set of quantum \
universal gates (",
 ButtonBox["Shi, 2003",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.5555/2011508.2011515"], None}],
 "; ",
 ButtonBox["Aharonov, 2003",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0301040"], None}],
 ")."
}], "Notes",
 CellID->1768381377,ExpressionUUID->"1143c652-c8cc-4d33-8d12-e53179238901"],

